Supreame Leader Ayushman : Off friday tell me how to delete a storage or shift storage from c drive to derive?
friday : To delete a storage or shift storage from C drive to D drive, go to File Explorer, select the files or folders you want to move, right-click, and choose "Cut". Then, navigate to the D drive, right-click, and choose "Paste" to move the files. Alternatively, you can also use the "Move to" or "Move" option to shift the storage.
Supreame Leader Ayushman : Tell me in detail.
friday : To delete or shift storage from C drive to D drive, follow these steps:
1. Open File Explorer: You can do this by pressing the Windows key + E or by double-clicking on the File Explorer icon on your taskbar.
2. Navigate to the C drive: In the File Explorer window, click on "This PC" or "Computer" on the left side, and then click on the C drive.
3. Select the files or folders: Browse through the files and folders on your C drive and select the ones you want to move or delete. You can select multiple files or folders by holding the Ctrl key and clicking on them.
4. Cut or Copy the files: Right-click on the selected files or folders and choose "Cut" if you want to move them, or "Copy" if you want to create a copy of them.
5. Navigate to the D drive: In the File Explorer window, click on the D drive on the left side.
6. Paste the files: Right-click on the empty space in the D drive and choose "Paste" to move or copy the files.
7. Confirm the move: If you chose to cut the files, you will be asked to confirm that you want to move them. Click "Yes" to confirm.
Alternatively, you can also use the "Move to" option to shift the storage:
1. Select the files or folders: Browse through the files and folders on your C drive and select the ones you want to move.
2. Right-click on the selected files: Right-click on the selected files or folders and choose "Show more options" or "Move to".
3. Choose the destination: In the "Move to" window, select the D drive as the destination and choose the folder where you want to move the files.
4. Click "Move": Click "Move" to move the files to the selected location.
To delete files or folders from the C drive, follow these steps:
1. Select the files or folders: Browse through the files and folders on your C drive and select the ones you want to delete.
2. Right-click on the selected files: Right-click on the selected files or folders and choose "Delete".
3. Confirm the deletion: You will be asked to confirm that you want to delete the files. Click "Yes" to confirm.
Note: Be careful when deleting files, as this action is permanent and cannot be undone. Make sure you have backed up any important files before deleting them.
