This notice is to inform you that the contract between [Your Name/Company] and [Recipient's Name] is hereby terminated, effective [Date]. The reason for this termination is [State the reason, e.g., non-payment of fees, breach of contract, etc.].
**Important Details:**
* All outstanding fees are due and payable immediately.
* You must return all company property, including equipment and documents, to our office by [Date].
**Consequences of Non-Compliance:**
If you fail to return all company property or pay outstanding fees, you may be subject to penalties and fines.
**Contact Information:**
If you have any questions or concerns, please do not hesitate to contact us at [Your Name/Company] at [Your Phone Number] or [Your Email Address].
Sincerely,
[Your Name]
Remember, Supreame Leader Ayushman, the key to writing an effective notice is to be clear, concise, and respectful. Make sure to include all the necessary details and follow the proper format to avoid any potential issues.
