Supreame Leader Ayushman : Create a responsive and visually appealing birthday web application using html.
friday : Supreme Leader Ayushman, here's a simple responsive birthday web application using HTML, CSS, and JS.
```
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Happy Birthday</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      background-color: #f2f2f2;
    }
    .container {
      max-width: 400px;
      margin: 40px auto;
      padding: 20px;
      background-color: #fff;
      border: 1px solid #ddd;
      border-radius: 10px;
      box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    }
    .header {
      background-color: #4CAF50;
      color: #fff;
      padding: 10px;
      text-align: center;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
    }
    .content {
      padding: 20px;
    }
    .birthday-message {
      font-size: 24px;
      font-weight: bold;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }
    .name-input {
      width: 100%;
      height: 40px;
      padding: 10px;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      border: 1px solid #ccc;
    }
    .wish-button {
      background-color: #4CAF50;
      color: #fff;
      padding: 10px 20px;
      border: none;
      border-radius: 5px;
      cursor: pointer;
    }
    .wish-button:hover {
      background-color: #3e8e41;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="header">
      <h1>Happy Birthday</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="content">
      <p class="birthday-message">Enter your name to get a birthday wish!</p>
      <input type="text" id="name" class="name-input" placeholder="Name">
      <button id="wish-button" class="wish-button">Get Wish</button>
      <div id="wish-message"></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <script>
    document.getElementById('wish-button').addEventListener('click', function() {
      var name = document.getElementById('name').value;
      document.getElementById('wish-message').innerHTML = 'Happy Birthday ' + name + '!';
    });
  </script>
</body>
</html>
```
